<p>I want to aggregate and count how often in my dataset is a special kind of disease at one date. (I don't use duplicate because I want all rows, not only the duplicated ones)</p>  <p>My original data set looks like:</p>  <pre><code>     id        dat   kinds kind AE00302 2011-11-20    valv    1 AE00302 2011-10-31    vask    2 </code></pre>  <p>(of course my data.frame is much larger)</p>  <p>I try this:</p>  <pre><code>xagg&lt;-aggregate(kind~id+dat+kinds,subx,length) names(xagg)&lt;-c("id","dat","kinds","kindn") </code></pre>  <p>and get:</p>  <pre><code>     id        dat kinds kindn AE00302 2011-10-31  valv     1 AE00302 2011-11-20  vask     1 </code></pre>  <p>I wonder why R is going wrong by the 'date' resp. the 'kinds'-column. </p>  <p>Has anybody an idea?</p>